  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "I have a use case where I'd like to create `N` resources where `N` == some value from values.yaml, e.g. `.Values.replicaCount` and have access to an `index`. For example, where `???` is the structure I'm missing, given a `replicaCount` int:\n\n``` yaml\n{{range $index, $element := ???}}\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: zookeeper-{{$index}}\n  namespace: {{.Values.global.namespace}}\n  labels:\n    release: {{ .Release.Name | quote }}\n    chart: \"{{.Chart.Name}}-{{.Chart.Version}}\"\nspec:\n  ports:\n    - name: client\n      port: 2181\n    - name: secure-client\n      port: 2281\n    - name: followers\n      port: 2888\n    - name: election\n      port: 3888\n  selector:\n    app: zookeeper\n    server-id: \"{{$index}}\"\n{{end}}\n```\n\nFrom my research it looks like this currently isn't possible with Go templates.\n",
